      "content": "**Buzzed Summary**\n\nTo ensure trust and accountability in our governance process, we propose replacing the community member Felfireferret on the Safe(Wallet) Multisig with JRtrades, and replacing Felfireferret as Snapshot manager with Cryptohicca. This action is necessary due to a breach of trust where Felfireferret used his position for personal reasons, which compromised the integrity of the community’s decision-making process.\n\n**Abstract** \n\nThis proposal seeks to replace the current community-elected member, Felfireferret, from the Safe(Wallet) Multisig and the Snapshot manager role due to misconduct. JRtrades and Cryptohicca, who were the next most-voted community members in the respective original elections, will assume these positions. This change is vital to maintain the integrity of our governance system. Specifically, Felfireferret’s actions in deleting two community proposals without consent, following a personal dispute, have violated the trust placed in him by the community. This BIP proposes the immediate implementation of these replacements.\n\n**Motivation**\n\nThe motivation behind this proposal is to address a serious breach of trust by a community-elected member, Felfireferret. The community depends on its elected representatives to act in the best interest of all members. However, Felfireferret abused his power by deleting two proposals without the community’s knowledge or consent, following a personal vendetta against two members who abstained from voting on his proposal. This action undermines the principles of transparency, fairness, and trust that are central to our governance model. It is crucial to replace him with JRtrades and Cryptohicca, who have been democratically selected by the community, to restore confidence in the governance process.\n\n**Specification**\n\n**Overview**\n\nThis BIP proposes the immediate replacement of Felfireferret on the Safe(Wallet) Multisig with JRtrades, and the replacement of Felfireferret as Snapshot manager with Cryptohicca. Both JRtrades and Cryptohicca were the next most-voted candidates in the original proposals that elected the Safe(Wallet) Multisig members and Snapshot managers. The proposal also includes an audit of recent governance actions to ensure no further unauthorized actions have been taken.\n\n**Rationale**\n\nThe decision to replace Felfireferret is based on the principle of accountability. His actions have demonstrated a disregard for the community’s trust, which is unacceptable for someone in such a critical position. JRtrades and Cryptohicca were chosen because they were the next most-voted candidates, ensuring that the replacements reflect the community’s original democratic choices. This approach minimizes disruption while restoring integrity to our governance process.\n\n**Technical Specification**\n\nSafe(Wallet) Multisig: Replace the current key assigned to Felfireferret with JRtrades.\n\nSnapshot Manager Role: Update the Snapshot system to remove Felfireferret’s access and grant it to Cryptohicca.\n\n**Test Cases**\n\nVerify that JRtrades has been correctly added to the Safe(Wallet) Multisig and can execute transactions. Ensure Cryptohicca can manage the Snapshot proposals and no longer allow access to Felfireferret.\n\nCopyright Copyright and related rights waived via CC0.",
