*: Production and bottling - $3,500 donation\n\n- **FelFireFerret (Project Lead)**: Oversight, marketing content - 1,000+ hours, $4,000\n\n\n\nThis is an economically viable project created out of sheer commitment of a team with creativity and dedication. A total of 300 bottles were sold during the 3 day event, also over 100litres were sold on tap between 3 different locations, spreading the BBH brand to people still out of our environment. The timing and access to an international theatre festival “Imaginarius”, also helped broadening the reach and to create a bridge for future actions.\n\n\n\nTotal Compensation Requested: $10,000 equivalent in a token most convenient to the BBH DAO (i.e. ETH, USDC, DAI)\n\n\n\n## -> Rationale\n\nThe project blends BBH branding with craft beer, aligning with BBH's black and yellow theme. The team has invested significant time and resources into ensuring the beer's success. This compensation acknowledges their efforts and supports future profitable productions. The team commitment to negotiate at least three future editions (according to BBH’s needs and time availability) ensures the DAO's initial investment will be recouped and generate profits.\n\n\n\n## -> Technical Specification (for future runs)\n\n- **Production Plan**: 500 bottles per run, production cost $4 per bottle, selling price $10 per bottle\n\n- **Potential Revenue**: $5,000 per run, $3,000 profit per run\n\n- **Investment Recoupment**: Initial $10,000 investment expected to be recouped within three runs\n\n[The previous values are according to a simple replication of what has been done. Adaptations can incur in a higher cost to provide a bigger profit margin but always below the market price for these services]\n\n\n\n**Marketing Strategies**:\n\n- Leverage BBH’s community for initial sales\n\n- Partnerships with craft beer festivals or other relevant events\n\n- Utilize social media and generate contents\n\n- Implement AR/Gamification for engagement\n\n\n\n## -> Tes